def: One of the Northmen who founded a dynasty in Russia in the 9thcentury; also, one of the Northmen composing, at a later date, theimperial bodyguard at Constantinople.
The convexity of a ship behind, under the stern. Mar. Dict.
A cumbrous two-wheeled pleasure carriage used in Cuba.
Relating to, or involving, crimination; accusing; as, acriminatory conscience.
Uncustomable; also, not having paid duty or customs. Smollett.
The segment of the body of an insect to which the wings areattached; the thorax. Kirby.
A garden of herbs; a cottage garden. T. Warton.
Wearied; tired; fatigued. [Obs.]Requickened what in flesh was fatigate. Shak.
